# Implementation Plan: Performance Optimization (Area 1) & Advanced Spatial Analytics / SAHI (Area 3)

This plan outlines the system-level optimizations and algorithmic improvements required to reduce execution latency, throttle heavy SQLite database commits, and introduce high-altitude small object detection (SAHI) without overloading the edge or backend CPUs.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key Architectural Choices & Impact:**
> 1. **ONNX Runtime Migration:** We will configure the backend to use `onnxruntime` instead of PyTorch (`ultralytics` native inference) for CPU execution. ONNX Runtime provides significant speedups on CPU.
> 2. **Slicing Aided Hyper Inference (SAHI) Overhead:** Sliced inference is computationally heavy since it runs YOLO multiple times per frame. We will implement **Dynamic SAHI**—it will only trigger when the drone's altitude exceeds a pre-defined threshold (e.g., 50 meters) where objects appear tiny.
> 3. **SQLite Write Batching:** To avoid thread pool exhaustion, we will batch database transactions every 5 seconds rather than committing at 3 Hz.

